0-30_p016_52fdfd6f,glyptic,seal,unknown,none,Late Antiquity,5th century,0-30.pdf,16,"Seal, material not specified, stamp seal of irregular form, measuring 1.8 cm in height, 1.2 cm in width, and 0.5 cm in thickness dated to the 5thâ€“6th century.","Seal with inscription, chalcedony, South Arabian, 6th-5th century BCE. The seal is pierced lengthwise and could have been mounted on a finger ring or strung on a necklace as an amulet. The inscription is transliterated as l-B'n and translated as ""Belonging to Ba'an."" Only the middle section of the seal is readable. Dimensions: 1.8 x 1.2 x 0.5 cm.",https://art.thewalters.org/object/42.1512/,metmuseum.org,194,0.351506,0.0687118,0.210109,combined score,metmuseum.org,New York,USA,museum
