0-22_p011_683adcce,jewelry,ring,unknown,none,Post-medieval / Modern,19th century,0-22.pdf,11,"Manuscript, paper, Hebrew, 19th century. A bound manuscript containing a gathering of manuscripts and holy books from Yemen, including Third Megillot (Song of Songs, Ruth and Ecclesiastes) with commentary by Talmud, Rashi, and later combined commentaries such as Mahary Tsalakh, as well as Parashat Peshit's papers with an adult explanation the volume includes material at the beginning and end of the manuscript.","Three manuscripts, on paper and gevil, from Yemenite Jewry, comprising a compilation of Scriptures and Targum. The group includes three Megillot, Shir HaShirim, Ruth and Kohelet, with Targum, Rashi commentary, and compiled novellae attributed to Mahari Tzalach and others Bereshit with Targum and Rashi commentary, with Haftarot and Targum of Shir HaShirim, Ruth and Kohelet. Two of the manuscripts are approximately 23-24 cm in size. Leaves of Parshat Bereshit with Rashi commentary are bound at the beginning and end of one manuscript. One manuscript has a gevil cover from the geniza of a Sefer Torah.",https://www.kedem-auctions.com/en/content/three-manuscripts-yemen,kedem-auctions.com,205,0.250832,0.000309348,0.12557,combined score,kedem-auctions.com,Jerusalem,Israel,auction
