0-22_p008_e6f7e902,manuscript,manuscript,unknown,none,Post-medieval / Modern,19th century,0-22.pdf,8,"Manuscript, paper, Hebrew and Arabic, Yemen, 19th century. The page describes three Yemeni manuscripts listed under this number at auction: a Hebrew manuscript with instructions and comments in the margins a manuscript with Arabic instructions and a colophon on the last page and a manuscript described as an Easter text with a Jewish translation into Arabic. All are on paper and dated to the 19th century.","Three manuscripts, Passover Haggadah, Yemenite, handwritten on paper. The group includes a manuscript described as ""A nice bakashah, praise to the King..."", by Rabbi Yitzchak ben Yefet, with instructions and commentaries on the margins, some with nikud elyon a second handwritten Haggadah and a third manuscript, Passover Haggadah, with Judeo-Arabic translation, lacking at the beginning and at the end. Size and condition vary, with overall fair condition.",https://www.kedem-auctions.com/en/content/three-manuscripts-passover-haggadah-yemen,kedem-auctions.com,202,0.201328,0,0.100664,score_txt only,kedem-auctions.com,Jerusalem,Israel,auction
0-22_p009_ab2ed43b,manuscript,manuscript,unknown,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-22.pdf,9,"Hebrew manuscript on paper, dated 1848, comprising 227 leaves and written in two columns per page with red ink headings and dialects. The manuscript includes red and black decorative elements at the beginning of each Nir, except Nirs VI and VII, and a framed title page (blonin) bearing the inscription that the book was written in Sana'a in 1848. Copies of the writer appear at the end of the book. It is described as a complete manuscript of formation, lacking a number of index leaves, and predating the well-known Livorno edition. Condition is noted as good.","Manuscript on paper, Menorat HaMaor by Rabbi Yitzchak Abuhav, written in Sana'a, Yemen, 1848. The manuscript is described as complete, apart from a number of index leaves missing at the end. At the beginning of each Ner, or chapter, there is red and black ornamentation, with the exception of the sixth and seventh Ners. The title page is illustrated with a two-colour frame and states that the book Menorat HaMaor was written by Rabbi Yitzchak Abuhav the Sephardi and written here in Sana'a in 1848. The text notes that Menorat HaMaor was widely embraced by Yemenite Jews and read in synagogues on Shabbat afternoon.",https://www.kedem-auctions.com/en/content/manuscript-menorat-hamaor-sanaa-yemen-1848,kedem-auctions.com,203,0.464569,0.0449033,0.254736,combined score,kedem-auctions.com,Jerusalem,Israel,auction
0-22_p012_ec9c65d5,manuscript,manuscript,unknown,none,Post-medieval / Modern,19th century,0-22.pdf,12,"Hebrew manuscript on paper, two Yemeni manuscripts wrapped in the original skin, comprising liturgical and devotional texts. The first manuscript contains Piyyutim of Bakashot, Tikun Chatzot, interpretation of tekufot, shtarot, ""Chiddushin,"""" Birkat Hamazon with Chiddushin, a eulogy, and a set of comments it is dated 1864, includes different owner signatures, comprises 131 leaves, measures approximately 16.5 cm, and is in fair condition with bleeding, tears, and stains, with an old leather binding and popular decoration. The second manuscript contains piyyutim of Selichot and Hosha'anot, is dated to the 19th/20th century in Yemen, comprises approximately 168 leaves, measures about 16.5 cm, and is in good condition.""","Manuscript, paper, with original leather binding. Yemen, 19th century. Two Yemenite manuscripts with original leather bindings, containing piyyutim of Bakashot, Tikun Chatzot, interpretation of dreams, tekufot and amulets, blessings and versions of shtarot, Birkat HaMazon with ""Chiddushin"", eulogies, and a compilation of commentaries. The manuscripts also include prayers and piyyutim of Selichot and Hosha'anot. One scribe's colophon names ""Ya'ish son of Yichye Al Tza'adi"" and is dated 1864. The bindings are described as ancient leather bindings with leather loops and adornments, worn and wormed, with folk ornamentation. Provenance: Collection of Willy Lindwer.",https://www.kedem-auctions.com/en/content/two-manuscripts-prayers-and-piyyutim-yemen-19th-century,kedem-auctions.com,206,0.244002,4.41074e-05,0.122023,combined score,kedem-auctions.com,Jerusalem,Israel,auction
0-22_p014_f8a5f56a,manuscript,manuscript,unknown,none,Post-medieval / Modern,19th century,0-22.pdf,14,"Manuscript, paper Hebrew manuscript for liturgical use throughout the year, including weekdays, Saturday, and festivals, in Yemeni writing in an animated letter, dated to the 19th century and measuring 17 cm. The manuscript contains a title page with the text ""Seder of the hall according to the Safari tradition, written throughout the year..."""" and, on the back of the title page, """"A copy of the lounge and the lounge according to our traditions in prayers throughout Yemeni cities."""" It includes a weekly and Saturday service, Rosh Chodesh service, Birkat HaLevana, Seder Lashanah, Tekun Burim, Tekun Besash with Al-Hajdah, prayers for the three festivals, and the Zikhrot for Shaft. Some leaves were later replaced by another hand several leaves are missing. The manuscript is in separate leaves, unbound, with spots, holes, tears affecting the text of several leaves, and engravings.""","Manuscript, siddur on paper for year-round use, Yemen, 19th century. The manuscript includes prayers for weekdays and Shabbat, prayers for Rosh Chodesh, Birkat HaLevana, Seder for Chanuka, Tikun Purim, Tikun Pesach with the Haggadah, prayers for the Three Festivals, and Azharot for Shavuot. The verso of the title page bears the note: ""Version of blessings and prayers, according to our tradition of the holy congregation throughout Yemenite cities"". The title page has an illustrated frame and is inscribed: ""Siddur of prayers according to Sephardic tradition, and written for the entire year..."". The last approximately 20 leaves, containing prayers for the Festival of Shavuot and Azharot, are in a different handwriting, and some leaves at the end were replaced in another handwriting. The manuscript shows stains, wear, and tears affecting the text of several leaves.",https://www.kedem-auctions.com/en/content/manuscript-siddur-year-round-use-yemen-19th-century,kedem-auctions.com,207,0.315857,0.0225565,0.169207,combined score,kedem-auctions.com,Jerusalem,Israel,auction
0-22_p016_cc4b6a73,manuscript,manuscript,unknown,none,Post-medieval / Modern,19th century,0-22.pdf,16,"Hebrew manuscript on paper, 19th century, comprising 8 elements of differing size and condition. The elements vary in situation some retain old ties, while others are newly associated. The manuscript is noted as being suitable for the equitable poor.","Manuscript collection, paper and bindings, comprising eight manuscripts from Yemen. The group includes Torah and Megillot, Passover Haggadot, and prayers. The manuscripts are described as a collection of eight items, with some volumes retaining old bindings and others newly bound. The source identifies the material as manuscripts and notes their association with Yemenite Jewry and manuscripts and documents.",https://www.kedem-auctions.com/en/content/collection-manuscripts-yemen,kedem-auctions.com,209,0.460173,0,0.230086,score_txt only,kedem-auctions.com,Jerusalem,Israel,auction
