0-25_p084_712079d1,object,unknown,unknown,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-25.pdf,84,"Lot, art, dimensions 14.2 Ã— 23.8.","Head, alabaster, hand-carved in high relief, perhaps from a funerary stele. The object presents a male visage with gazing almond-shaped eyes beneath thin brows, a slender nose above pursed lips, protruding rectangular ears, and a stocky neck. The surface is described as quixotic in expression, and the head is noted as stylistically similar to another example with comparable facial hair stippling. The text identifies this type of figural representation as belonging to a tradition of alabaster and other stone stele with high relief faces honoring the deceased. Size: 5.6 in. W x 9.375 in. H (14.2 cm x 23.8 cm).",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/Fine-South-Arabian-Alabaster-Head-of-Bearded-Male/77f-fine_south-09.5.19-artemi,lot-art.com,46,0.489321,0,0.24466,score_txt only,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-25_p085_f13f7dbe,object,unknown,bronze,bull,Unclassified,unknown,0-25.pdf,85,"Hooves, bronze. A group of identical oversized bull hooves in bronze, each larger than normal size and larger than a large cube. Two examples have prominent holes above the cube for installation, and three examples are hollow inside, with holes at the back of the cubes and on the foot base.","Four cast bronze bull hooves, each more-than-life-sized and similarly proportioned, with a realistic hoof form showing two claws, a cuboid element set slightly over the back of the hoof, and two naturalistic projections from the rear. Two of the examples have projecting slots on top of the cuboid, indicating attachment points. The form suggests that they may have served as supports for a table or altar rather than for a full bull statue another possibility is that they belonged to a naos, a simple rectangular temple form. Each measures 5.75 in. W x 11 in. H (14.6 cm x 27.9 cm). The group is dated broadly to the 1st millennium BCE to the early 1st millennium CE, probably later in that range based on the lead weight mentioned in the source text.",https://www.bidsquare.com/online-auctions/artemis-gallery/set-of-4-sabean-bronze-bull-hoof-supports-2251316,bidsquare.com,47,0.252536,0.0844908,0.168513,combined score,bidsquare.com,New York,USA,platform
