0-30_p012_4aa6b43c,sculpture,statue,bronze,human,Late Antiquity,6th century,0-30.pdf,12,"Human statue, bronze, 6th century B.C.E. Height 24 cm. Condition: good.","Bronze votive statue of a man, South Arabian, 6th century B.C. This ex-voto sculpture represents a standing male figure with the right arm bent and the left arm held close to the body the fists are clenched and pierced. The figure is dressed in a pleated loincloth moulded to the hips and extending to the knees, crossed and open at the front, and secured by a belt. The dating given in the source is supported by the stylistic treatment of the garment, whose drapery recalls the Achaemenid friezes of Persepolis, and by the hairstyle, described as volute-like curls comparable to those of Assyrians, Persians, and Greeks of the 6th century B.C.",https://www.artcurial.com/en/sales/2266/lots/72-a,artcurial.com,191,0.282503,0.174953,0.228728,combined score,artcurial.com,Paris,France,auction
