0-30_p021_65971c7e,sculpture,statue,bronze,none,Late Antiquity,5th century,0-30.pdf,21,"Animal statue, bronze, 5th century B.C.E. The object is an animal statue in bronze. Dimensions: height 12.8 cm, width 3.8 cm, depth 7.4 cm base dimensions: width 3.3 cm, depth 5.8 cm.","Figure of ibex, bronze, ca. 5th century BCE. This small bronze sculpture depicts an ibex standing on a base, with distinctive long horns turning back to touch the upright ears. It is from Southwestern Arabia and measures H. 5 1/16 × W. 1 1/2 × D. 2 15/16 in. (12.8 × 3.8 × 7.4 cm) base: W. 1 5/16 in. × D. 2 5/16 in. (3.3 × 5.8 cm). The object may have served as a handle for an incense burner.",https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/324255,metmuseum.org,198,0.364715,0.0472301,0.205972,combined score,metmuseum.org,New York,USA,museum
0-22_p004_4c5b844c,sculpture,statue,marble,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-22.pdf,4,"Statue, marble, 12.1 x 19.1 cm, dated to 200â€“100 B.C.E. Rectangular marble statue of a woman with a clearly defined face the front is broad at the eyes and narrows to a hard, pointed chin. The eyes are set beneath arched eyebrows and retain light-coloured residue the nose is very long with a high bridge. The eyebrows are engraved, and a single line across the upper forehead appears to indicate a headband or similar head covering.","Bust, alabaster. Sabean alabaster bust of a woman, dated 200 BCE–100 CE, measuring 12.1 x 19.1 cm (4 3/4 x 7 1/2 in). The object depicts a feminine head and neck and is described as a striking head that may have served as a grave marker or perhaps as a commemorative piece from the ancient kingdom of Saba in southwestern Arabia, centered in modern-day Yemen. Detailing is limited, with incised eyebrows and a single line at the apex of the forehead that appears to suggest a headband or similar feature. The text also notes that it may once have formed part of a larger alabaster structure.",https://barakatgallery.eu/artworks/54789-sabean-alabaster-bust-of-a-woman-200-bce-100-ce/,barakatgallery.com,201,0.324405,0.0453292,0.184867,combined score,barakatgallery.com,London,UK,dealer
0-22_p022_e2eb1dc8,sculpture,statue,unknown,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-22.pdf,22,"Statue, material not specified, depicting a woman standing on a rectangular base, with a pointed face, a prominent nose bridge extending to the eyebrows, and a bunch of facial features rendered in an obvious, stylized manner dated to the first century BC height 31 inches (79 cm).","Female votive figure, marble with an applied gesso layer painted with coloured details, standing frontally on a small rectangular integral plinth and dated to circa 1st century B.C. The figure wears a long dress, waisted and ending at the calves above ankle bracelets, with incised linear and cross-hatched ornament over the legs and around the upper arms. She is shown with strands of necklaces composed of triangular pendants and a large central crescentic pendant above the breasts, and her arms are bent at the elbows with the forearms projecting forward to hold a rectangular hollowed-out votive bowl with incised panels. The oval face has a pointed chin, strong browline, incised arched brows, large eyes with drilled pupils, a straight nose, and a small mouth. The hair flares below the ears and falls to the shoulders, with incised linear banded details and a diadem of circular pendants above the forehead. Height: 31 in (79 cm).",https://www.bonhams.com/auctions/21928/lot/129/,bonhams.com,215,0.228755,0.0975569,0.163156,combined score,bonhams.com,London,UK,auction
