29- _29_p021_11b31839,sculpture,statue,bronze,human,Unclassified,unknown,29- _29.pdf,21,"Human statue, bronze, representing a warrior of Sparta with a brown shield and edged border. The statue is described as the oldest witness of Greek art in ancient Yemen. Height 17 cm.","Bronze statuette of a warrior, Archaic period, 17 cm high, from Yemen. The figure is identified as a warrior and is described as being seen from the left, since the double moulding on the left side of the helmet crest does not appear to have been repeated on the right side. It is suggested that the figure may originally have belonged to a larger composition, either as a counterpart to another figure on the rim of a vessel or as part of a free-standing group. The object has been discussed in relation to Laconian bronzes and published by Beazley and Jucker.",https://www.georgeortiz.com/objects/greek-world-cont/117-warrior-archaic/,georgeortiz.com,220,0.247423,0,0.123712,score_txt only,georgeortiz.com,Geneva,Switzerland,collection
29- _29_p043_255b10d7,sculpture,statue,marble,bull human,Unclassified,unknown,29- _29.pdf,43,"Human statue, marble. Human statue in marble, dated to the first century BC. Height 20.9 cm. Condition: good.","Head, carved striped alabaster, with the facial features reduced to a simplified form: a slender neck rising to a rounded chin, a compact mouth with a small moustache above the upper lip, a ridge nose, almond-shaped eyes, and a sweeping incised brow. The top of the head is flattened. The object is raised on a bespoke mount and measures 20.9 cm high excluding the stand. The source text identifies it as an Ancient Sabaean Arabian male head from Southern Arabia, dated to around the turn of the first millennium B.C., and notes that it was intended to fit within a small rectangular niche within a ritual site, serving as a votive object.",https://www.lyonandturnbull.com/auctions/form-through-time-735/lot/31,lyonandturnbull.com,221,0.344739,0,0.172369,score_txt only,lyonandturnbull.com,Edinburgh,UK,auction
0-14_p027_ec708607,sculpture,statue,marble,bull horse,Unclassified,unknown,0-14.pdf,27,"Animal statues, marblestone. Four animal statues of different sizes and shapes, depicting a dog, a bull, and a horse, all standing on rectangular bases except the bull. First century BC. Largest 12 cm.","Animal figures, South Arabian, four in total, with the largest example measuring 12 cm. No further details on material, technique, date, or condition are provided in the source text.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/FOUR-SOUTH-ARABIAN-ANIMAL-FIGURES/45-four_south-15.7.22-plaka,lot-art.com,224,0.389138,0.0265663,0.207852,combined score,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p029_f769888f,sculpture,statue,marble,human,Unclassified,unknown,0-14.pdf,29,"Human statue head, marble stone, carved in the round with a blindfolded treatment likely from a statue. The head has two horizontal eyebrows with incised lines, a nose that is largely broken, a small visible horizontal upper lip, and a shallow horizontal line indicating the mouth opening. Ears are visible on both sides.","Head, alabaster, South Arabian, of a man, 3rd century B.C./1st century A.D. The object is drilled underneath and mounted on a black marble base. It has large eyes recessed for inlay and grooved, drilled eyebrows. Condition noted in the source includes damage to the chin and nose, slight abrasions to the ear rims, and a large shallow chip on the back. The reverse bears the inscription or mark ""CB 10"" in black ink.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-South-Arabian-Alabaster-Head-of-a-Man--3rd-Century-BC1st-Century-AD/20-south_arabian-07.12.21-sotheby,lot-art.com,226,0.345337,0,0.172669,score_txt only,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p030_c5cb9878,sculpture,head,unknown,none,South Arabian Antiquity,3rd century,0-14.pdf,30,"Oyster, carved material, with the heads rendered very prominently and accurately, and the feet and chests carved small, visible, and light dated to the 3rd century B.C. to 1st century A.D.","Architectural block, limestone, carved in relief on one side with a frieze of five stylised frontal ibexes. The animals are depicted with straight legs in low relief, stepped muzzles, protruding circular eyes, and ribbed horns. South Arabian, dated to the 3rd century B.C./1st century A.D. The object is heavily encrusted, with chips on the lower part of three muzzles.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-South-Arabian-Limestone-Ibex-Frieze--3rd-Century-BC1st-Century-AD/2-south_arabian-07.12.21-sotheby,lot-art.com,227,0.435036,0,0.217518,score_txt only,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p032_82525ee5,sculpture,statue,marble,human,South Arabian Antiquity,3rd century,0-14.pdf,32,"Human statue head, marble stone, carved with inlaid gemstone eyes the eyebrows are rendered as two drifting horizontal lines, the nose is prominently carved, broad at the base, and the mouth is indicated by a horizontal line below. Marble stone. 3rd century B.C. / 1st century A.D.","Relief head, alabaster, South Arabian, circa 3rd century B.C./1st century A.D. The object depicts a woman's head in relief and is carved in alabaster. It has large eyes inlaid with calcite and green stone, with one inlay remaining, grooved eyebrows, long hair, and a necklace. The description identifies the piece as South Arabian and dates it to the circa 3rd century B.C./1st century A.D.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-South-Arabian-Alabaster-Relief-Head-of-a-Woman--circa-3rd-Century-BC1st-Century-AD/19-south_arabian-07.12.21-sotheby,lot-art.com,228,0.328385,0,0.164192,score_txt only,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p035_4c0a409e,sculpture,statue,unknown,human,Unclassified,unknown,0-14.pdf,35,"Statue, material not specified, depicting a human face with a prominent head, frontal features, button-like details, and a mouth carved in a small, visible, smiling manner the front is marked by a blade-like line running from left to right with the letters L./Bester. Dated to the third to first century B.C.","Stele, marble, South Arabian/Sabaean, with inscription, 10.8 cm long. Funerary or memorial stele depicting a stylised face in high relief. The face has a flat forehead, bulging eyes, extended eyebrows merging at the centre of the face into a long nose, and a closed mouth with broad lips. On the forehead, the name is inscribed upside-down in the tradition of tomb dedications, with Sabaean letters reading the name Sarhan (SRHN). The object is identified as South Arabian/Sabaean and dated broadly to the pre-Islamic period.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/South-ArabianSabaean-Marble-Head-Stele-with-Inscription--c-3rd-1st-Century-BC/75-south_arabian-28.2.23-artemission,lot-art.com,229,0.321506,0,0.160753,score_txt only,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p038_e61326bd,sculpture,statue,limestone,human,Unclassified,unknown,0-14.pdf,38,"Human statue head, limestone. Head of a human statue carved in limestone, with poorly carved eyes, two eyebrows rendered as a prominent arched form, a prominent nose, and a mouth represented by an empty horizontal line. Dated from the 3rd century BC to the 1st century AD.","Stone head with typical South Arabian characteristics, carved with a somber countenance, almond-shaped eyes, arched brows, a straight nose, high cheekbones, and a closed mouth. The head is flanked by a pair of high-set ears and has a chin-length coiffure. Dimensions are 2.4 in W x 2.5 in H (6.1 cm x 6.4 cm).",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/South-Arabian-Stone-Head/98-south_arabian-11.5.23-artemi,lot-art.com,232,0.323314,0,0.161657,score_txt only,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p041_6240297d,sculpture,statue,marble,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-14.pdf,41,"Statue, marble stone: oak statue on a rectangular base, with a prominent head hanging forward, two prominent eyes, and two curved horns extending to the back and beneath the ears.","Ibex, alabaster, South Arabian, circa 1st century A.D. The object is described as an ibex carved in alabaster. Its height is given as 5 3/8 inches (14 cm), and the height with stand is recorded as 5.8 inches (15 cm).",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-South-Arabian-Alabaster-Ibex-Height-5-38-inches-14-cm/69-south_arabian-26.5.22-hindman,lot-art.com,235,0.404895,0.0942011,0.249548,combined score,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
0-14_p044_dfa1c7a5,sculpture,statue,limestone,human,Unclassified,unknown,0-14.pdf,44,"Human statue, limestone. Human figure seated, carved in limestone broken at the organs. The figure has two inset eyes. First century AD.","Female figure, limestone, South Arabian, circa 3rd century B.C.–1st century A.D. The figure is made of limestone and preserves remnants of a dark resin on the face. The source text notes that a comparable female figure in the British Museum has a brown coating identified by chemical analysis as containing plant oils and conifer resins, suggesting either a conifer resin varnish mixed with oils or an oil perfumed with resin applied in thick layers. The object is recorded as 24 cm high.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-South-Arabian-limestone-female-figure/256-south_arabian-06.7.23-bonham,lot-art.com,238,0.318815,0.0639966,0.191406,combined score,lot-art.com,Amsterdam,Netherlands,platform
