0-25_p095_9ee6e6c7,stone monument,tombstone,marble,human,Unclassified,unknown,0-25.pdf,95,"Tombstone, marble stone, with a human face in relief or incised depiction showing a broad long rectangular nose, two visible eyes with indicated pupils, a small mouth, and a wide chin below the face is a two-line inscription. The object is described as a marble tombstone and is dated to about 200 BCE.","Funerary stele, alabaster, South Arabian, ca. 200 BC-200 AD. The stele bears a stylised low-relief depiction of the deceased's face, with the eyes and nose emphasised. The object is described as a South Arabian alabaster funerary stele. Recorded size: length 190 mm, width 120 mm.",https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/SOUTH-ARABIAN-ALABASTER-FUNERARY-STELE/396-south_arabian-05.11.23-apollo,barakatgallery.com,53,0.414496,0.057753,0.236124,combined score,barakatgallery.com,London,UK,dealer
