0-5_p001_9cc546a5,stone monument,tombstone,marble,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-5.pdf,1,"Tombstone, marble, fragmentary, with incised inscription and relief decoration described as a man's tombstone, preserving part of the deceased's name with the letter ""N"""" visible in the final line, and featuring a human face motif with prominent eyes, a small mouth, and a strand or line beneath the mouth. Provenance is given as the southern Arabian Peninsula (old Yemen). Length 27.5 cm.""","Stela, alabaster. Fragment of a sculpted stela depicting a stylized frontal face with a long straight nose and hollow eyes originally intended for inlay. The base preserves part of a South Arabian inscription, identified in the source as the owner's name. South Arabian Peninsula, late 1st millennium BC. Height: 27.5 cm.",https://www.pba-auctions.com/en/lot/10456/2145504?offset=250&,pba-auctions.com,92,0.388024,0,0.194012,score_txt only,pba-auctions.com,Unknown,USA,auction
0-5_p002_883e543c,stone monument,tombstone,marble,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-5.pdf,2,"Statue head, marble: head of a male statue with a long neck, carved in marble the face has high eyebrows, prominent eyes, a prominent nose, and a small mouth, with hair rendered in a clear, salty tombstone-like treatment.","Iconic head, material not specified. This small-scale head was generally mounted on inscribed limestone bases bearing the owner's name. The present example represents a man with short hair exposing the ears. The face is triangular in shape, with a long, slender nose above a short mouth, and a beard collar in slight relief rising to the ears. Height: 12.5 cm.",https://www.pba-auctions.com/lot/15546/2983798?refurl=T%C3%8ATE+ICONIQUE.+Elle+repr%C3%A9sente+un+homme+%C3%A0+la+coiffure+courte+d%C3%A9gageant+les+oreilles.+Le+visage+trian,pba-auctions.com,93,0.342823,0,0.171411,score_txt only,pba-auctions.com,Unknown,USA,auction
