0-30_p017_6c61750c,stone monument,tombstone,stone,none,South Arabian Antiquity,2nd century,0-30.pdf,17,"Tombstone, stone, dated to around the 2nd century B.C.E., with a height of 32.4 cm.","Stele, limestone, South Arabian, rectangular in form and sculpted at the upper end with the head of a bearded man in high relief. The beard and hair are rendered by echeloned curls, and the face has a sharp brow, long triangular nose, thin closed lips, raised eyes with deeply recessed pupils. An inscription below identifies the deceased. Dated circa 2nd century B.C.-2nd century A.D. Height 123⁄4 in. (32.4 cm.).",https://www.christies.com/en/lot/lot-4205318,christies.com,195,0.374337,0.0885842,0.231461,combined score,christies.com,London,UK,auction
0-22_p018_439e9ea8,stone monument,tombstone,marble,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-22.pdf,18,"Tombstone, marble. Carved funerary monument depicting a male bust in relief, with short hair at the back, a round face, heavy eyelids, a prominent nose, and a small mouth. Dated to around the 1st century B.C./A.D.","Object group, various materials: a mixed antiquities lot comprising Roman glass vessels, including a large green glass jug, an aubergine glass jug, and an aubergine ribbed glass bottle Roman bronze objects, including a figure of Minerva and an incense burner with dolphin handle Egyptian objects in wood, limestone, alabaster, bronze, turquoise faience, green glazed faience, pale green glazed faience, and cartonnage, including shabtis, a Ptah-Sokar-Osiris figure, a kneeling king statuette, an amulet of Bastet, and painted mummy masks Luristan iron and bronze objects, including swords and a horsebit a South Arabian bronze erotic statuette a South Arabian alabaster head a Near Eastern copper alloy pectoral and a Late Roman or Byzantine solid gold bracelet with agate cabochon. The source text gives no measurements or further technical details beyond typology, material, and named attribution where stated.",https://www.bonhams.com/auctions/20021/lot/283,bonhams.com,211,0.440125,0.0529293,0.246527,combined score,bonhams.com,London,UK,auction
0-22_p023_23c77c9b,stone monument,tombstone,marble,none,Unclassified,unknown,0-22.pdf,23,"Tombstone, marble. Carved tombstone depicting a woman's grave with a long neck, an oval face with clearly defined facial features, including eyebrows carved above the eyes, a white-stone inlay, a long straight nose, and a small mouth.","Head, alabaster. South Arabian Qatabanian alabaster head of a woman, circa 1st century B.C./A.D. The object is carved with a long neck and an oval face, the features rendered in a stylised manner. It has arching incised eyebrows above almond-shaped eyes inlaid with white stone, a long straight nose, and a small mouth below. The hair falls behind semi-circular ears. The head is mounted on an alabaster stepped base. The overall height, including the base, is 29.5 cm.",https://www.bonhams.com/auctions/23364/lot/147/,bonhams.com,216,0.42377,0.134897,0.279334,combined score,bonhams.com,London,UK,auction
